Spring Grain Sowing in Russia Plunges 55%, According to Interfax

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-04-04T10:50:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/spring-grain-sowing-in-russia-plunges-55-according-to-interfax.html
The pace of spring grain sowing in
 Russia  fell by more than half from a year earlier, Interfax
reported, citing Agriculture Ministry figures.  Spring grains covered 346,700 hectares (856,714 acres) as
of today, down 55 percent from the same date last year, the news
agency said. The seeded area was 763,300 hectares a year ago,
according to Interfax.  Sowing in the Krasnodar region slid to 230,000 hectares
from 316,000 hectares last year, Interfax said. In the Stavropol
region, planting dropped to 91,000 hectares from 207,000
hectares last year, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
